Three security guards were killed while two others sustained injuries on Wednesday, June 9 after suspected thugs raided Kivaywa Secondary School in Kakamega County.   Edward Malala,40, Henry Khaoya, 55 and Evans Wanyonyi, 56, were killed by suspected thugs while Situma Sitikho and Luca Wanjala are admitted at Webuye County Hospital following the attack.  During the raid, the suspects stole a TV set, one laptop, a public address system and some cash all valued at about Sh150,000.  While confirming the incident, Matete OCPD Thomas Ototo said police have begun a probe into the incident which took place on Wednesday night.  Police officer commits suicide at work  Kenyan international goalkeeper Matasi breaks silence after car crash  Oparanya dismisses ODM claims Bukhungu stadium built by government  Mother hangs self after setting house on fire with her four children inside “Our officers visited the school and have started investigations into the incident,” he said.  The bodies of the three were moved to Webuye Hospital Mortuary on Thursday morning.   Murder Mystery: FBI joins investigations into the disappearance & murder of Bashir Mohammed  Police detain a couple and their son for allegedly beating their 15-year-old daughter to death  The widow of Jacob Juma has accused police of dragging their feet in the hunt for Juma’s killers By Nathan Ochunge | 3 hours ago By Robert Amalemba | 4 days ago By Brian Kisanji | 5 days ago By Nathan Ochunge | 5 days ago